shing Square is expected to price its IPO; Barclays, BP, Foxconn and GM report earnings. </p><p style=\"margin-top:24px;font-size:16px\"><strong style=\"font-size:16px\">Wednesday:</strong> Rate decisions from the US as well as Brazil, Canada and Thailand; the Eurozone reports economic and consumer confidence; Meta, Alphabet, Amazon, Microsoft, Samsung, Deutsche Bank and AstraZeneca report earnings. </p><p style=\"margin-top:24px;font-size:16px\"><strong style=\"font-size:16px\">Thursday: </strong>A number of countries release GDP (the US, Taiwan, Spain, Mexico, Saudi Arabia) and unemployment (Brazil, Colombia, the Eurozone, Germany, Israel); the US and Eurozone will both release inflation data; China releases April PMI; the ECB and BOE announce rate decisions; Apple and Eli Lilly release earnings. </p><p style=\"margin-top:24px;font-size:16px\"><strong style=\"font-size:16px\">Friday:</strong> The UK and US release manufacturing PMI; Japan reports CPI; financial markets closed in several regions for May Day public holiday; Estée Lauder and Exxon release earnings.<strong style=\"font-size:16px\"> </strong></p><h2 style=\"font-size:24px;line-height:30px;font-weight:700;padding-top:12px;border-top:1px solid;margin-top:40px\">Weekend Reads</h2><div style=\"max-width:580px;margin-top:24px;margin-bottom:16px\"><div style=\"padding:16px 0;border-bottom:1px solid #ccc;padding-top:0\"><a href=\"https://links.message.bloomberg.com/a/sc/WiV6n4MN2NhGq2EWb6OWcUUZ7qxY4t0TBxkWrwX6vWDA7CUe5Bwd0tkdPpkPA_As1d95sodaFJdFGJCvFRHEttBcr4bNtM1mlPwHhBJ7Uial7dVDa44hCh0zt1_r9dWINMmozVV7gLDptuL0q_3FbttfaQ-MOW-1xhnfEZCU5e9E0GkGGpJEatEFQ46Co4yunXlD8fwmVRk5zPzBZWYIcBJTqhdWgCT1uMRJThF3QewX5-0RVhknM7JLa3Pj3roITpXDXyRHvFXRKLs5NZtTDx7crziAzMzLmpIH-cfgKg7LPK-mskV6ceFyjRMVeWc35nyvgkZ3EW-oIerNAhSJz4PdigJb/yQ6xPnhaHjhaeNEGhmJMrGhxBKoK7m4M/20\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"text-decoration-line:underline;text-decoration-style:solid;font-size:inherit;color:inherit;text-decoration:none\"><div style=\"overflow: